/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:24:- The example identity `u . grad u = grad(|u|^2 / 2) - u x omega` is textbook. After projection, the gradient is removed and one is left with the Lamb-vector term. That does not by itself reduce derivative count or remove quadraticity; it just relocates them.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:25:- Helmholtz projection is order zero. It can expose cancellations, but it does not automatically transform a second-order CZ-type obstruction into a first-order gain. The step is written as though the right rewrite might make the problem "gain-bearing" by algebra alone. That is the main hidden assumption, and it is weak.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:27:- Scale counting is not enough. A symbol can look first-order under naive counting and still fail once the relevant truncation, commutator, or nonlocal pressure reconstruction is applied. This step needs estimate-level testing, not just identity-level algebra.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:30:Concrete failure mode: Step 2 may conclude that a projected Lamb-vector form is "best" because it isolates the nonlinearity cleanly, but that is largely cosmetic unless the chain shows an actual improvement on the bad localized term rather than a cleaner decomposition.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:44:### Step 4 - Apply the Tao filter and close the chain
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:46:Including the Tao filter is correct, but putting it last is a structural mistake.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:48:- Many of the candidate mechanisms named earlier are already close to "energy + harmonic analysis + classical algebraic rewriting." Those are precisely the things Tao's averaged model is designed not to distinguish. The filter should be used before spending budget on Step 2 and certainly before drifting into Step 3.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:49:- The chain only uses one direction of the Tao filter. If a mechanism survives averaging, it is blocked. Fine. But if averaging destroys the mechanism, that does not mean the mechanism is strong enough to matter for regularity. The current step risks treating "not Tao-blocked" as a positive signal when it is only a necessary condition.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-02.md:63:The real issue is not whether an identity exists, but whether it improves the localized/truncated interaction that blocks the proof. That question appears only in Step 3. Steps 1 and 2 can therefore consume budget on identities that are obviously harmless at the PDE level but useless at the proof level.
